en_8313539_0	Colombo (News 1st): SriLankan Airlines announced that flights between Sri Lanka and Pakistan will not operate until Monday (March 4).
en_8313539_1	Pakistani air space continues to remain closed.
en_8313539_2	Pakistan’s Civil Aviation Authority closed its air space last week as a security measure during the Pakistan – India crisis.
en_8313539_3	SriLankan Airlines further noted flights will commence again as soon as Pakistan opens its air space.
